# My Sample Markdown

## Introduction
This is a demonstration of different Markdown formatting options. Let's explore some common elements you might use in your documents.

### Text Formatting
You can make text **bold** or *italic*. You can also combine them for ***bold italic*** text. ~~Strikethrough~~ is also possible.

### Links and Images
Here's [a link to Google](https://www.google.com)
And here's how you embed an image:
![Alt text for an image](https://example.com/image.jpg)

### Code Blocks
Here's some inline `code` and a code block:
```python
def hello_world():
    print("Hello, World!")
    return True
```

### Blockquotes
> This is a blockquote.
> It can span multiple lines.
> Each line starts with a '>' character.

### Tables
| Header 1 | Header 2 | Header 3 |
|----------|----------|----------|
| Cell 1   | Cell 2   | Cell 3   |
| Cell 4   | Cell 5   | Cell 6   |
